European Coal Derivatives Fall 1%, First Drop in Three Sessions

-- B y   A l i s t a i r   H o l l o w a y
-- 
2011-04-26T14:44:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/european-coal-derivatives-fall-1-first-drop-in-three-sessions.html
Benchmark European coal derivatives
fell for the first time in three sessions.  Coal for delivery to Amsterdam, Rotterdam or Antwerp with
settlement next year dropped $1.35, or 1 percent, to $129.65 a
metric ton by 3:28 p.m. in  London .  The data are drawn from information supplied by ICAP Plc,
 GFI Group Inc. (GFIG) , Spectron Group Ltd., Credit Suisse Group AG, IHS
McCloskey, Bloomberg, Tradition Financial Services and Tullett
Prebon Plc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alistair Holloway in London at 
 aholloway1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  